parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Engine overheating can cause damage to engine components, leading to costly repairs, and in severe cases, can lead to engine failure and even fires, posing a significant risk to vehicle occupants and other road users.
symptoms: flames or smoke coming from under the hood

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Piston failure can cause engine failure, leading to costly repairs, and potentially leaving the driver stranded.
Engine oil leaks can cause damage to engine components, leading to costly repairs, and potentially causing accidents due to oil spills on the road or slippery pedals.
EGR solenoid failure can cause poor engine performance, decreased fuel efficiency, and potentially lead to engine damage.
Gasket failure can cause engine oil leaks, coolant leaks, or other fluid leaks, leading to engine damage and potentially causing accidents.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Engine Stalling and Ignition System Failure
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Engine stalling can cause loss of power, loss of control, and increase the risk of accidents, especially when driving at high speeds. Ignition system failure can lead to difficulty starting the engine or cause the engine to stall, which can leave the driver stranded.
symptoms: Engine stalls or dies while driving
spark plugs fouled or worn out

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Battery failure can cause the engine to stall or fail to start, leaving the driver stranded and potentially causing accidents or injuries.
symptoms: engine stalls or dies while driving.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: ECM failure can cause the engine to stall or malfunction, leading to loss of power, loss of control, and increased risk of accidents.
symptoms: Engine stalls or dies while driving
